(6) The issues and failures associated with communism and
autocratic governments;
(7) The continued failure of communism and autocratic
governments resulting from the direct influences of the following without
limitation:
(A) The Union of Soviet Socialist Republics and its
successor state, Russia;
(B) The People's Republic of China;
(C) Democratic People's Republic of Korea; and
(D) Argentina; and
(8) The natural deterioration of democracies into autocracies
over history, including without limitation in Afghanistan, the Democratic
Republic of the Congo, Haiti, Somalia, Sudan, and Yemen."
AND
